# Cloud Handoff Protocol

When coordinator sessions exceed Cloud migration limits, orchestrate via [docs/AGENT_DISPATCH_LOG.md](../../docs/AGENT_DISPATCH_LOG.md) and copy-paste prompts — do not assume session continuity in Cloud.

## Planning rule

Every coordinator plan (`CreatePlan` output) must include an **Execution mode** column in the task table (or per-todo tag).

| Mode | Who |
|------|-----|
| `COORDINATOR_LOCAL` | Coordinator in current chat |
| `COORDINATOR_AGENT` | Subagent/Task spawned locally |
| `MANUAL_CLOUD_AGENT` | User opens new Cursor Cloud agent |
| `USER_LOCAL` | Product owner (manual prod/smoke) |
| `BLOCKED` | Waiting on dependency |

## Coordinator duties

- Choose execution mode **per task** before execution
- `MANUAL_CLOUD_AGENT` → output full copy-paste prompt using [Manual Cloud Agent Task Template](../../docs/AGENT_DISPATCH_LOG.md#manual-cloud-agent-task-template) + [Prompt Footer](../../docs/AGENT_DISPATCH_LOG.md#standard-cloud-agent-prompt-footer); never assume Cloud auto-starts
- `BLOCKED` → state dependency explicitly in dispatch log
- Prod SHA updates → always `COORDINATOR_LOCAL` or post-deploy coordinator step, **never** Cloud
- Session start / after Cloud finish → run [coordinator sync command](../../docs/AGENT_DISPATCH_LOG.md#coordinator-sync-command)

## Hard rules (Cloud agents)

- Never deploy, secrets, or push to `master` — PR only
- Coordinator owns prod state; prod SHA only after verified deploy

See [docs/CLOUD_AGENT_SETUP.md](../../docs/CLOUD_AGENT_SETUP.md) and [docs/CURSOR_COORDINATOR.md](../../docs/CURSOR_COORDINATOR.md#cloud-handoff-protocol).
